  Provincial secretary of Sadtu Nomarashiya Caluza has harshly criticised the circular issued by the department of education of freezing the appointment of teachers during the last term. The circular has since been withdrawn.
 


Caluza said they had taken notice of the matter and how the department continued to make announcement that affect employees without an input from the unions.

"This is something that we will not stand for," she said. 
She said the last term was a critical period in any school where important work was still being done. She added that preparations for the following year were being seen to. 

"This needs to be done with no mistakes and it is unreasonable to burden teachers with more work loads," she said. 
The Mercury